  • Constructor Details

    • SolveAProd

      public SolveAProd(int strt, int stop, double[] y, double[] x, int[] ptr, double[] sprs, int[] xIndx, TreeMapIntegerDouble[] tm)
      Parallel task that solves aProd both either forward or backward for an arbitrary number of rows or columns. If solving for the row oriented "u" vector then strt and stop are the beginning and ending rows to process, y is "u", x is "v", ptr is aRowPtr, sprs is aRowSprs, and xIndx is aColIndx. If solving for the column oriented "v" vector then strt and stop are the beginning and ending columns to process, y is "v", x is "u", ptr is aColPtr, sprs is aRowSprs, and xIndx is aRowIndx.
      Parameters:
      strt - First row or column to process by this task.
      stop - Last - 1 row or column to process by this task.
      y - The vector to be modifed ("u" or "v").
      x - The vector multiplying the sparse vector to modify y ("v" or "u").
      ptr - The row or column pointer vector.
      sprs - The row oriented or column oriented sparse matrix.
      xIndx - The column index or row index vector to indirectly address into x.

  • Method Details

    • call

      public LSQRTester.PartialResult call()
      The parallel call that will perform the aProd multiply of the sparse matrix aSpM times the x input vector aX. The result is set into the vector aY.
